name: magnesium chelatase
reaction: ATP + protoporphyrin IX + Mg2+ + H2O = ADP + phosphate + Mg-protoporphyrin IX + 2 H+ [RN:R03877]
comment: This is the first committed step of chlorophyll biosynthesis and is a branchpoint of two major routes in the tetrapyrrole pathway.

references.title: In vitro assay of the chlorophyll biosynthetic enzyme Mg-chelatase: resolution of the activity into soluble and membrane-bound fractions.
references.journal: Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U. S. A. 88 (1991) 5789-93.

references.title: Interplay between an AAA module and an integrin I domain may regulate the function of magnesium chelatase.
